Method Detail

sendMessage

public void sendMessage(java.lang.Object msg)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
Send the message to the remote server. This method tries to hide the connection latency. If it's already connected, then the message is sent immediately. Otherwise, the message is temporarily buffered in the this.pendingMessages. Once it's connected, the buffered messages are sent to the server.

Specified by:

Parameters:
